    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's... that's exactly it. \"Letting the darkness take you.\" Every single day feels like I'm just performing these tasks, like eating or cleaning, but I'm just a ghost. It's like I've already died, I'm just still walking around. Does it ever actually stop being this heavy? Or is this just what the rest of my life is supposed to be?",
